                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p class="text-secondary lh-lg m-0" style="text-align: justify;">
                                        This research proposal outlines a comprehensive security evaluation of public
                                        and private key infrastructure deployed across modern IoT smart home frameworks.
                                        By analyzing potential edge execution nodes, the study aims to identify
                                        cryptographic latency trade-offs alongside physical and data-driven security
                                        configurations. The experimental design relies entirely on simulated machine
                                        states and open-source protocol packages.
